From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 08:50:00 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] arm64: dts: mediatek: gemini: keep MT6351 rails in regulator node

Patch 0051 adds the disabled RT5735 candidate but accidentally changes the
existing eMMC regulator consumers from the MT6351 `regulators` child to the
PMIC parent. That produces invalid `mediatek,mt6397` schema placement and
would prevent the MT6351 regulator binding from owning the rails. Restore the
existing regulator-container parent; the RT5735 node remains on I2C7.

Signed-off-by: Julien Etienne <julien.etienne@gmail.com>
---
 arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
--- a/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
+++ b/arch/arm64/boot/dts/mediatek/mt6797-gemini-pda.dts
@@ -123,4 +123,4 @@
-&pmic {
+&mt6351regulator {
 	mt6351_vemc_reg: ldo-vemc {
 		regulator-name = "vemc_3v3";
 		regulator-min-microvolt = <3000000>;
-- 
2.43.0
